        "content": "\nNo test exercises the screen transitions or key handling at all.\n\n```go\nfunc TestHandleKey_Picking(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"down\"))\n    if m.cursor != 1 {\n        t.Fatalf(\"cursor = %d, want 1\", m.cursor)\n    }\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\" \"))\n    if !m.selected[1] {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected selected[1] = true after space\")\n    }\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\" \")) // toggle back off\n    if m.selected[1] {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected selected[1] = false after second space\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_PickingBounds(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.cursor = 0\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"up\")) // must not go negative\n    if m.cursor != 0 {\n        t.Fatalf(\"cursor = %d, want 0\", m.cursor)\n    }\n    m.cursor = len(providers) - 1\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"down\")) // must not exceed len(providers)-1\n    if m.cursor != len(providers)-1 {\n        t.Fatalf(\"cursor = %d, want %d\", m.cursor, len(providers)-1)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_EnterWithNoneSelectedSelectsAll(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"enter\"))\n    if m.countSelected() != len(providers) {\n        t.Fatalf(\"expected all %d providers selected, got %d\", len(providers), m.countSelected())\n    }\n    if m.screen != screenLimit {\n        t.Fatalf(\"screen = %v, want screenLimit\", m.screen)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_LimitScreen_InvalidInput(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.screen = screenLimit\n    m.limitInput.SetValue(\"not-a-number\")\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"enter\"))\n    if m.screen != screenLimit {\n        t.Fatal(\"invalid limit input must not advance the screen\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_LimitScreen_NegativeRejected(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.screen = screenLimit\n    m.limitInput.SetValue(\"-1\")\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"enter\"))\n    if m.screen != screenLimit {\n        t.Fatal(\"negative limit must be rejected\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_LimitScreen_ZeroIsValid(t *testing.T) {\n    // 0 means \"unlimited\" per the flag doc — must NOT be rejected\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.selected[0] = true\n    m.screen = screenLimit\n    m.limitInput.SetValue(\"0\")\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"enter\"))\n    if m.limit != 0 || m.screen != screenRunning {\n        t.Fatalf(\"limit=%d screen=%v, want limit=0 screen=screenRunning\", m.limit, m.screen)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_LimitScreen_EscReturnsToPicking(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.screen = screenLimit\n    m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"esc\"))\n    if m.screen != screenPicking {\n        t.Fatalf(\"screen = %v, want screenPicking\", m.screen)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_QuitBlockedWhileRunning(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.screen = screenRunning\n    m.pending = 1\n    _, cmd := m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"q\"))\n    if cmd != nil {\n        t.Fatal(\"q should be a no-op while providers are still running\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestHandleKey_QuitAllowedWhenDone(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.screen = screenRunning\n    m.pending = 0\n    _, cmd := m.handleKey(keyMsg(\"q\"))\n    if cmd == nil {\n        t.Fatal(\"q should quit once pending == 0\")\n    }\n}\n\n// keyMsg is a small helper — tea.KeyMsg has no public constructor from a string,\n// so build via tea.Key{Type: ...} or the appropriate helper for the bubbletea version in go.sum.\nfunc keyMsg(s string) tea.KeyMsg { /* TODO: construct from s */ return tea.KeyMsg{} }\n```\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "3. `Update()` message handling — `tui.go:96`",
        "content": "\n```go\nfunc TestUpdate_StatusMsgAppendsLineAndSetsRunning(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.statuses[\"midi-madagasikara\"] = &providerStatus{state: stateIdle}\n    m.runOrder = []string{\"midi-madagasikara\"}\n    m.Update(statusMsg{provider: \"midi-madagasikara\", line: \"fetching page 1\"})\n    st := m.statuses[\"midi-madagasikara\"]\n    if st.state != stateRunning || len(st.lines) != 1 {\n        t.Fatalf(\"state=%v lines=%v\", st.state, st.lines)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestUpdate_DoneMsgError(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.statuses[\"midi-madagasikara\"] = &providerStatus{state: stateRunning}\n    m.pending = 1\n    m.Update(doneMsg{provider: \"midi-madagasikara\", err: errors.New(\"boom\")})\n    st := m.statuses[\"midi-madagasikara\"]\n    if st.state != stateError || m.pending != 0 {\n        t.Fatalf(\"state=%v pending=%d\", st.state, m.pending)\n    }\n    if !strings.Contains(st.lines[len(st.lines)-1], \"boom\") {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected error line appended\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestUpdate_DoneMsgSuccess(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.statuses[\"midi-madagasikara\"] = &providerStatus{state: stateRunning}\n    m.pending = 1\n    m.Update(doneMsg{provider: \"midi-madagasikara\", err: nil})\n    if m.statuses[\"midi-madagasikara\"].state != stateDone || m.pending != 0 {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected stateDone and pending=0\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestUpdate_WindowSizeMsgRecomputesViewport(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    m.Update(tea.WindowSizeMsg{Width: 100, Height: 40})\n    if m.width != 100 || m.height != 40 {\n        t.Fatal(\"width/height not updated\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\nNote: `statusMsg`/`doneMsg` handlers do `m.statuses[msg.provider]` and immediately dereference `st.state = ...` with **no nil check**. If a message ever arrives for a provider not in `m.statuses` (e.g. a stray goroutine message after a restart, or a race between `startRun` populating the map and a goroutine already sending), this **panics on nil pointer dereference**. Worth a defensive test + fix:\n\n```go\nfunc TestUpdate_StatusMsgForUnknownProvider_DoesNotPanic(t *testing.T) {\n    m := newModel(10, \".\")\n    defer func() {\n        if r := recover(); r != nil {\n            t.Fatalf(\"Update panicked on unknown provider: %v\", r)\n        }\n    }()\n    m.Update(statusMsg{provider: \"does-not-exist\", line: \"x\"})\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "4. `runCrawler` — `main.go:59` (currently zero coverage, shells out to `uv run main.py`)",
        "content": "\nRefactor-for-testability note: it hardcodes `\"uv\"` as the binary. To unit test without `uv`/python installed, either (a) put a fake `uv` shim on `PATH` for the test, or (b) extract the `exec.Command` construction behind a seam. Given \"don't over-engineer,\" the shim approach is the lower-footprint option:\n\n```go\nfunc TestRunCrawler_StreamsLines(t *testing.T) {\n    dir := t.TempDir()\n    writeFakeUV(t, dir, `#!/bin/sh\necho \"line one\"\necho \"line two\"\nexit 0\n`)\n    withPathPrepended(t, dir)\n\n    var got []string\n    err := runCrawler(\"provider-x\", 5, \".\", func(line string) { got = append(got, line) })\n    if err != nil {\n        t.Fatalf(\"unexpected error: %v\", err)\n    }\n    if len(got) != 2 || got[0] != \"line one\" || got[1] != \"line two\" {\n        t.Fatalf(\"got %v\", got)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestRunCrawler_NonZeroExitReturnsError(t *testing.T) {\n    dir := t.TempDir()\n    writeFakeUV(t, dir, `#!/bin/sh\necho \"failing\"\nexit 1\n`)\n    withPathPrepended(t, dir)\n\n    err := runCrawler(\"provider-x\", 5, \".\", func(string) {})\n    if err == nil {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected non-zero exit to surface as error\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestRunCrawler_StderrFoldedIntoSameStream(t *testing.T) {\n    dir := t.TempDir()\n    writeFakeUV(t, dir, `#!/bin/sh\necho \"to stderr\" 1>&2\nexit 0\n`)\n    withPathPrepended(t, dir)\n\n    var got []string\n    _ = runCrawler(\"provider-x\", 5, \".\", func(line string) { got = append(got, line) })\n    if len(got) != 1 || got[0] != \"to stderr\" {\n        t.Fatalf(\"expected stderr line folded in, got %v\", got)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestRunCrawler_BinaryNotFound(t *testing.T) {\n    withPathPrepended(t, t.TempDir()) // empty dir, no `uv` on PATH\n    err := runCrawler(\"provider-x\", 5, \".\", func(string) {})\n    if err == nil {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected error when uv is not on PATH\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestRunCrawler_InvalidCrawlerDir(t *testing.T) {\n    err := runCrawler(\"provider-x\", 5, \"/definitely/does/not/exist\", func(string) {})\n    if err == nil {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected error for nonexistent crawler-dir\")\n    }\n}\n\n// writeFakeUV / withPathPrepended: TODO helpers to drop an executable `uv` script\n// into dir and prepend dir to $PATH for the duration of the test (t.Setenv).\n```\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "5. `runHeadless` — `main.go:80` (concurrency + output, zero coverage)",
        "content": "\n```go\nfunc TestRunHeadless_AllProvidersRun(t *testing.T) {\n    dir := t.TempDir()\n    writeFakeUV(t, dir, `#!/bin/sh\necho \"ok\"\nexit 0\n`)\n    withPathPrepended(t, dir)\n\n    out := captureStdout(t, func() {\n        runHeadless([]string{\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"}, 1, \".\")\n    })\n    for _, name := range []string{\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"} {\n        if !strings.Contains(out, \"[\"+name+\"]\") {\n            t.Errorf(\"missing output for provider %q\", name)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestRunHeadless_PartialFailureDoesNotBlockOthers(t *testing.T) {\n    // one provider's fake uv exits 1, others exit 0 — runHeadless must still\n    // report all providers and must not hang/panic when one fails.\n    // TODO: per-provider PATH override isn't possible with a single `uv` shim;\n    // requires refactoring runCrawler to take an injectable command name/dir,\n    // or naming providers such that the shim script branches on os.Args[2] (provider name).\n}\n```\n\nThis surfaces the real gap: `runHeadless` has **no synchronization on stdout** across goroutines — `fmt.Printf` from concurrent goroutines isn't guaranteed to interleave at line granularity for longer output. Worth a `-race` run and, if it matters, a test asserting no torn lines under concurrent load with long strings.\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "6. Integration test gaps",
        "content": "\n- **Full TUI flow, headless-driver style**: use `github.com/charmbracelet/x/exp/teatest` (not currently a dependency — would need adding) to drive `newModel` through `picking → limit → running` with real `tea.Program.Send`, asserting final rendered output contains expected provider names/counts. This is the only way to catch bugs in the interaction between `Update`, `View`, and the real Bubble Tea event loop (current unit tests above call `handleKey`/`Update` directly, bypassing the program's message pump).\n- **`startRun` → goroutine → `program.Send` → `Update` round-trip**: `startRun` (`tui.go:254`) is entirely untested. It's the seam where background goroutines feed the model via `m.program.Send`. A test needs a real `tea.Program` (or a fake with a `Send` capturing channel) since `m.program` is `nil` in a bare `newModel`, which means `startRun` would nil-panic if invoked without `p.program = p` first — this init-order dependency (`main.go:50`) is itself untested and easy to break.\n- **End-to-end with the real Python crawler**: none of the above stub `uv` calls exercise the actual `apps/crawler/main.py` contract (line format, `--limit` semantics, exit codes). A slower, opt-in (`-tags=integration` or build-tag-gated) test invoking the real crawler against a stub/local news source would catch drift between the Go and Python sides — currently the only coupling documented is the comment at `main.go:15-17` about `providers` mirroring `PROVIDERS` in Python, with no automated check that the lists stay in sync.\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
      {
        "title": "Summary of gaps by priority",
        "content": "| Priority | Gap | Risk |\n|---|---|---|\n| High | `Update` nil-deref on unknown provider (`tui.go:108,117`) | Panic crashes the whole TUI |\n| High | `runCrawler` error paths (binary missing, bad dir, non-zero exit) | Silent hangs/misreported failures in a script meant for cron |\n| Medium | `truncate` byte-slicing on multi-byte strings | Panic/garbled output if a provider name ever has non-ASCII chars |\n| Medium | Screen-transition state machine (`handleKey`) | Regressions in keybindings ship silently |\n| Medium | `runHeadless` concurrent stdout writes | Interleaved/torn log lines under load |\n| Low | Pure helpers (`articlesSaved`, `countSelected`, `highlighted`, `layout`) | Low risk but zero-cost to cover, good regression net |\n| Low | Provider-list drift between Go (`main.go:18`) and Python `PROVIDERS` dict | Silent mismatch, not caught by any test |\n\nNo test infra exists yet — first step would be adding a `main_test.go` / `tui_test.go` under this same package (not a new dir, per project convention) and, if the full TUI integration tests are wanted, adding `github.com/charmbracelet/x/exp/teatest` to `go.mod`.",
        "level": 3
      }
    ],
